This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of natural language processing (cs.CL) because it focuses on analyzing the impact of semantic representation bias in occupation classification using machine learning. It may also belong to the sub-category of cybernetics (cs.CY) because it deals with potential allocation harms that can result from bias in machine learning algorithms. Additionally, it could be classified under social and information networks (cs.SI) because it studies the impact of gender bias on online biographies. The paper also involves statistical learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) as it uses machine learning techniques to analyze the data.
